originalText.text:
Maybe their night life is better than their day time lunch hours. I called ahead to see if they serve turkey burgers and was happy to hear that they do! I walked in around 2PM and the energy and hospitality was lack luster, as I was told to seat myself wherever. Initially I went to the bar where I was told happy hour does not begin until 4PM and only drinks will be served. So, I find a quiet spot in the corner between the threshold of the bar and dining room. The water glasses are already facing right side up on the table, and visibly dirty. I just asked for a clean glass, no problem. Iâ€™ll take partial responsibility for the fact that I was served a turkey burger with pork bacon on it. I ordered blindly without reading the menu, but I feel as though I shouldâ€™ve been informed by my knowledgeable waitress. Regardless, I sent it back knowing they were just going to remove the bacon from my burger and reassemble it accordingly. To my dismay, my burger comes back with a hair on the plate. Mind you, itâ€™s only 2PM. Iâ€™m sure it wasnâ€™t intentional but at this point the cleanliness of this establishment is a cause for concern.

In the end my meal was compensated, and I was no longer planning to leave this review due to  their effort to rectify the situation. However, the opportunity presented itself when I was notified to leave a reviewðŸ˜…

Have a wonderful lunch experience at Harlem Tavern. The food was ready in about 10 minutes and was delicious. They have several screens showing sports games.
Staff were very accommodating as we had children with us.

originalText.text: First time visiting, even though I pass by alot. Waitstaff was friendly. Atmosphere was good, especially for a weekday. My friend had the truffle fries, BBQ spare ribs and Harlem tavern sliders. I had the beef nachos (pictured). Solid prices. Recommended.

originalText.text:
This is a busy local hot spot. My visit was on a Sunday during brunch. Tables were available but we opted for the bar to be away from the crowds. The Shocktop beer on draft was cold and delicious. I highly recommend the pot of mussels in spicy tomato sauce.  It is served with garlic bread to soak up that great broth. Aside from that, we ordered fries, chicken, and waffles, which were all great as well.

Looking forward to returning soon.

originalText.text:
I had late lunch there. The place was packed (I now think it's because Sunday football was on) so I assumed the food and drinks were good. I ordered  "A Peach Grows In Harlem" as my cocktail and chicken and waffles. The drink was a sugary mess and you could hardly taste the alcohol. There wasn't a balance of ingredients in the cocktail. The waffles were good but the chicken was not at all appetizing. The first bite I took of the chicken skin was like rubber. I kept chewing but the fibers weren't breaking down so I gave up and spat it out.  I tried a different piece and noticed that parts of the chicken were over cooked and others were under. It felt and tasted stale. And whatever batter they used also tasted like it hadn't been changed in a while. I could literally taste the flour. This is experience was disappointing. I won't be back except maybe for beer or wine (not cocktails.)
**Someone in my party did have the gumbo and enjoyed it, though.
